22 Sec. 4. (1) There is hereby levied upon and there shall be
23 collected from any person engaged in the business of providing
24 accommodations to transient guests in a convention hotel, whether
25 or not membership is required, an excise tax at the following
26 rates:
27 (a) For a convention hotel located within a qualified local
28 governmental unit, under section 9(4), the following:
29 (i) A rate of 3% of the room charge for accommodations in a
